pgTitle: Flag of the governor-general of New Zealand

rows.text: Flag of the Governor of New Zealand. The Union Jack defaced with four white stars in the form of a cross.
File:Flag of the Governor of New Zealand (1874-1908).svg
Flag of the Governor of New Zealand. The Union Jack defaced with a white circle with four red stars and the initial 'NZ' in the center. The whole surrounded by a green wreath.
File:Flag of the Governor of New Zealand (1908–1936).svg
Flag of the Governor of New Zealand. The Union Jack defaced with a white circle with four red stars and the initial 'NZ' in the center. The whole surrounded by a wreath of fern.
File:Flag of the Governor-General of New Zealand (1936–1952).svg
Flag of the Governor-General of New Zealand. The crest from the royal coat of arms of the United Kingdom, a crowned lion standing on the Tudor crown. With 'Dominion of New Zealand' in a scroll below.
File:Flag of the Governor-General of New Zealand (1953-2008).svg
Flag of the Governor-General of New Zealand. The crest from the royal coat of arms of the United Kingdom, a crowned lion standing on the St. Edward's crown. With 'New Zealand' in a scroll below.
